svg.title: Edward Montagu, Lord Chief Justice, temp. Henry VIII, died 1557. Son of Edward Montagu: Edward Montagu, Knt., “A worthy patriot in the reign of Queen Elizabeth,” died 1602. Children of Edward Montagu, Knt.: Edwd. Montagu, Knt., First Lord Montagu of Boughton. Walter, Knt. Henry, Lord Montagu, First Earl of Manchester. Charles, Knt. James, Bishop of Bath 1605, and Winchester 1616. Sidney, Knt., M.P. for Huntingdon in the Long Parliament, whence he was expelled. Mar. Paulina, daughter of John Pepys, of Cottenham, Camb., died 1644. Children of Sidney, Knt.: Henry, drowned at sea. Edward, a distinguished Parliamentary Captain, M.P. for Huntingdon, Admiral. First Earl of Sandwich, died 1672. Elizabeth, mar. Sir Gilbert Pyckering, of Titchmarsh.
